'''Yvon Madiot''' (born 21 June 1962) is a former French [[bicycle racing|racing cyclist]].<ref name="ProCycling">{{cite web |url=http://www.procyclingstats.com/rider.php?id=154369 |title=Yvon Madiot |accessdate=27 April 2014 |work=ProCyclingStats}}</ref> He won the [[French National Road Race Championships|French national road race title]] in 1986,<ref name="CyclingArchives">{{cite web |url=http://www.cyclingarchives.com/coureurfiche.php?coureurid=1840 |title=Yvon Madiot |accessdate=27 April 2014 |work=Cycling Archives}}</ref> going on to finish tenth in that year's [[1986 Tour de France|Tour de France]].<ref name=renault>{{cite web |url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/features/renault-the-best-tour-de-france-team-ever/ |title=Renault: The best Tour de France team ever? |last1=Cossins |first1=Peter |date=22 July 2014 |website=[[cyclingnews.com]] |access-date=28 March 2016}}</ref>

He is the younger brother of fellow retired racing cyclist and double winner of [[Paris–Roubaix]], [[Marc Madiot]], and works alongside Marc as part of the management of the [[FDJ.fr]] cycling team<ref>{{cite web |url=http://autobus.cyclingnews.com/news.php?id=news/2004/jan04/jan28news1 |title=FDJeux.com team presentation |last1=Henry |first1=Chris |date=28 January 2004 |website=[[cyclingnews.com]] |accessdate=31 May 2014}}</ref> as an assistant sports director.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.uciworldtour.com/Modules/SUCI/TEAMS/TeamDetails.asp?id=MTI&RefDate=04.01.2012&MenuId=MTYzMDE&LangId=1&BackLink=%2Ftemplates%2FUCI%2FUCI2%2Flayout.asp%3FMenuId%3DMTYzMDE%26LangId%3D1 |title=UCI WorldTour: FDJ-Big Mat - (FRA) |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |website=[[UCI World Tour]]|accessdate=31 May 2014}}</ref> He has played a particularly important role in developing young riders, mentoring [[Arthur Vichot]], [[Jérémy Roy (cyclist)|Jérémy Roy]], [[Cédric Pineau]], [[Mathieu Ladagnous]], [[Mickaël Delage]], [[Arnaud Démare]] and [[William Bonnet]], among others.<ref name=renault />

